In her first interview about her engagement, Minnie has dished all the deets on her beau, confirming that he is indeed Quinton Jones, a cameraman who works for the Urban Brew production company. The pair have been dating for two years and started out as friends. Minnie told the Sunday Times they were smitten with each other and understood one another. &#8220;He has been my best friend for many years, and knowing that we are going to be spending the rest of our lives together is a fairy tale. &#8220;Quinton is very private and not a fan of the limelight but has always been incredibly supportive of my career.&#8221; ALSO READ: This is how Boity gets her incredible body Minnie has kept her relationship with Quinton under wraps, unlike her past romance with Bafana Bafana goalie Itumeleng Khune. She shied away from uploading images of him on her social media accounts, opting to keep the public guessing about who he was. One thing Minnie has made clear though is that Quinton is the love of her life. &#8220;We are constantly laughing and making fun of each other, but at the end of the day, wig off and no make-up, he still looks at me like I&#8217;m the most beautiful girl in the world.&#8221; For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.